column23: Facade engineering is more about structural, thermal and acoustic aspects of the same. Architectural impact should be defined as a small scope for facade engineering.
column35: Understanding the envelope performance is core to facade engineering
column142: Facade engineering should be part of civil engineering as much as and more than it is necessary for civil engineering. It is not enough to know basics of structural engineering, to be a good facade engineer. An architect can be a good facade architect, who understands correlation of engineering principles. To be a good facade engineer, it is important to be a strong structural engineer before anything else. Facades today are not simple systems. They require complex structural and movement analysis.
